'Cangjie programming language_generics_enum_generic_enum_definition': 'In Cangjie code language, In the design of generic enum types in the Cangjie programming language, the Option type is a typical example, and for a detailed description of Option, please refer to the Option type chapter. The Option type is used to indicate that a value of a type may be empty. In this way, Option can be used to represent a failure to compute on a certain type. It's uncertain what type of failure is here, so it's clear that Option is a generic type that needs to be declared as a type parameter.
As you can see, Option<T> is divided into two cases, one is Some(T), which is used to represent a return result with value, and the other is None which is used to represent an empty result. The getOrThrow function will be a function that returns the value inside Some(T), and the result returned is the T type, and if the parameter is None, then it will throw an exception directly.'

Code_Example:
package std.core // `Option` is defined in std.core.

public enum Option<T> {
      Some(T)
    | None

    public func getOrThrow(): T {
        match (this) {
            case Some(v) => v
            case None => throw NoneValueException()
        }
    }
    ...
}
